Fitness features

Cardio Load

Cardio load measures how hard your heart works each day. Compare trends over time to see if you are under- or overtraining. Receive a daily target based on your cardio load and readiness levels thats designed to balance recovery with performance.,

Heart rate on gym equipment

Connect Charge 6 to your favorite compatible exercise machine and see your real-time heart rate.

Compatible with select workout machines that support the Bluetooth Heart Rate Profile, and coming soon to more. See here for more information on Charge 6-compatible machines.

Daily Readiness Score

Find out if your body is ready to work out or needs time to recover. Available with Fitbit Premium.

40+ exercise modes

Track your favorite exercises like runs, bike rides, strength training, yoga, and more, and get live stats on your wrist.

Heart rate tracking

The heart of it all: Heart rate powers important data like calorie burn, sleep stages, resting heart rate, and more.

Active Zone Minutes

Tracks your time in heart rate zones so you get credit when you work harder. Workouts in cardio or peak zones earn double minutes.

Built-in GPS

See pace and distance on your wrist no phone needed.

Cardio fitness score

Estimate your fitness level using your VO2 max (how well your body uses oxygen during exercise).

SmartTrack Automatic Exercise Recognition (in app only)

Automatically recognizes your exercise and records it in the Fitbit app post-workout.

Water resistant

Youre covered to 50m, so dance in the rain if thats how you want to work out today.

Charge 6 is designed to comply with a water protection rating of 5 ATM under ISO standard 22810:2010 when manufactured, but it is not waterproof. Water resistance is not a permanent condition and decreases or is lost over time due to normal wear and tear, repair, disassembly or damage. Dropping your Charge 6 may result in loss of water resistance. Charge 6 is designed to be used in shallow water and should not be used for activities involving water at high velocity or high temperature. Some Charge 6 bands are not water resistant. See here for details.

Workouts on your phone

Sweat to high-energy workouts in the Fitbit app, from Fitbit trainers and popular partner brands. Most workouts require a Fitbit Premium membership.

Premium content and features may vary, recommendations are not available in all locales and may be in English only.

All-day activity tracking

Just get moving well take care of the rest. Charge 6 tracks your steps, distance, calories burned, and Active Zone Minutes 24/7.

Workout intensity map (in app only)

After outdoor exercise with GPS, check your workout intensity map in the Fitbit app to see your pace and heart rate zones throughout your route and learn where you put in the most effort.

Timer and stopwatch

Get instant access to tools that make your life easier like a timer for interval training and a stopwatch for tracking sets at the gym.

Health features

ECG app for heart rhythm assessment

The compatible ECG app lets you assess your heart rhythm for atrial fibrillation a heart rhythm irregularity and share results with your healthcare professional.

The ECG app and irregular heart rhythm notifications features are only available in select countries and with select Fitbit products; not intended for use by people under 22 years old. The irregular rhythm notifications feature is not intended for use by people with known atrial fibrillation. See here for additional details.

High and low heart rate notifications

If resting heart rate is above or below your usual range, youll get notified in the Fitbit app.

SpO2 (blood oxygen) tracking

Tracking SpO2 makes it easy to monitor your blood oxygen levels so you can know when there may be an important change in your wellbeing.

Not available in all countries. Not intended to diagnose or treat any medical condition or for any other medical purpose. Intended to help you manage your well-being and keep track of your information. Requires more frequent charging.

Skin temperature variation

Identifies changes in skin temperature, which can be related to activity, illness, menstrual cycle & more.

Only available in the Fitbit app and only displays variation. Not available in all markets. Not intended for medical purposes. Significant changes in ambient temperature may negatively impact skin temperature tracking.

Resting heart rate

An important indicator of your heart health and fitness. In general, active people have a lower RHR.

Breathing rate

Small variations in your breathing rate could be a sign of changes in your wellbeing.

Only available in select countries. Not intended for medical purposes or to diagnose or treat any medical condition. This feature is only intended to provide information to assist you with managing your wellbeing.

Irregular heart rhythm notifications

Checks for potential signs of an irregular heart rhythm that may be atrial fibrillation (AFib), so you can share this information with your healthcare provider.

The ECG app and irregular heart rhythm notifications feature are only available in select countries and with select Fitbit products; not intended for use by people under 22 years old. The irregular rhythm notifications feature is not intended for use by people with known atrial fibrillation. See here for additional details.

Blood glucose tracking (in app only)

Log your glucose levels and see how activity, sleep, stress, and nutrition impact your trends in the Fitbit app.

Advanced analytics available with Fitbit Premium. Available in select countries. Not a replacement for medical advice and not intended to diagnose or treat any medical condition. Intended to help you monitor and keep track of your information. Talk to your healthcare provider for more guidance.

Menstrual health tracking

Log periods, record symptoms, find patterns in your cycle, and estimate your ovulation window.

Not intended to be used for contraceptive or other medical purposes. May not accurately predict your menstrual cycles or related information. Intended only to help you monitor and keep track of certain information.

Health and wellness reminders

Activate optional personalized reminders for beneficial tasks that can be tough to remember, like staying hydrated, sticking to a sleep schedule, getting in activity and more. Feel like youve been sitting too long? Fitbits got you. A buzz on your wrist lets you know its time to move.

Sleep and stress features

Stress Management Score

See how well your bodys handling stress each day. Detailed score breakdown available with Fitbit Premium.

EDA scan app for stress management

Do EDA mindfulness sessions on your wrist to help you relax and get instant feedback on your stress.

Sleep Score

Learn about the quality of your previous nights sleep with a personalized Sleep Score.

Sleep Profile

Get matched with a sleep animal and see a personalized analysis of your sleep every month.

Requires Fitbit Premium membership. Not intended for medical purposes. Consult your healthcare professional for questions about your health.

Smart Wake alarm

Vibrating alarm wakes you during the optimal sleep stage so you feel refreshed.

Sleep tracking and sleep stages

Automatically tracks how long you sleep each night and time spent in light, deep, and REM sleep stages.

More helpful features

Do not disturb and sleep mode

Mutes calls and notifications and turns your screen off.

YouTube Music controls

DJ your workouts right from your wrist with YouTube Music controls. Start, stop, and skip over 100 million songs from the worlds largest music catalog.

Your compatible phone must be in Bluetooth range of your Fitbit device to use this feature. YouTube Music controls require a paid YouTube Music Premium subscription. YouTube Music streaming (non-premium version) on Charge 6 is currently available only in Canada and the U.S.

Google Maps

Easily get where youre going with an interactive view and turn-by-turn directions on your wrist.

Some Google apps and services require a paired phone within Bluetooth range of your device and are not available in all countries or languages. Data rates may apply.

Google Wallet

Make purchases from your wrist with Google Wallet.

Data rates may apply. Works with most phones running Android 11 or iOS 16.4 or newer. Requires Google Account and internet access. Google apps are not available in all countries or languages. Data rates may apply.

Call, text, and app notifications

See calls, texts, and smartphone app notifications on your wrist when your phone is nearby.

Works with most phones running Android 11 or iOS 16.4 or newer. Requires Google Account and internet access.

Color touchscreen

A bright color display for sharp stats all day.

Find My Phone

Find your phone without needing someone to call it for you.

Always-on display mode

Keeps your display on at all times (may require more frequent charging).

7-day battery life

Long battery life means less charging and more living.

Average battery life is approximate and is based on testing conducted in California in mid 2023 on pre-production hardware and software, using default settings with a median Fitbit user battery usage profile across a mix of talk, data, standby, and use of other features. Battery life depends on features enabled, usage, environment, and many other factors. Use of certain features will decrease battery life. Actual battery life may be lower.

Clock faces and accessories

Give your Fitbit a stylish new look with dozens of clock faces and accessory bands to choose from.

Compatible with iOS and Android devices

Fitbit devices are compatible with iOS and Android phones. Learn more.

Fitbit Premium membership

Level up your fitness with 6 months of Fitbit Premium. Get access to thousands of workouts like HIIT, cycling, dance cardio & more from Fitbits awesome trainers. Use your Daily Readiness Score to optimize your routine and get recommended workouts based on your score.

Fast Pair

Android users can use Fast Pair to help streamline setup and get going on their goals.

Fast Pair requires location enabled.
